<DialogueTree xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/xen-42/outer-wilds-new-horizons/main/NewHorizons/Schemas/dialogue_schema.xsd">
	<NameField>Cedar</NameField>

	<DialogueNode>
		<Name>5</Name>
		<EntryCondition>DEFAULT</EntryCondition>
		<Dialogue>
			<Page>Dear Skies! The prophecy! It has come true!</Page>
		</Dialogue>
		<DialogueOptionsList>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>The-The what?</Text>
				<DialogueTarget>2</DialogueTarget>
			</DialogueOption>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>Who ARE you?</Text>
				<DialogueTarget>3</DialogueTarget>
			</DialogueOption>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>Bye bye.</Text>
			</DialogueOption>
		</DialogueOptionsList>
	</DialogueNode>

	<DialogueNode>
		<Name>2</Name>
		<Dialogue>
			<Page>The prophecy, of course, as any seasoned Chirpian would know, is a story that has been passed down by generations of elders, depicting of a traveller from the unknown coming down from the skies to give us the ability to destroy our greatest fear and enemy: The Pot of Chaos.</Page>
		</Dialogue>
		<DialogueOptionsList>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>What's The Pot of Chaos</Text>
				<DialogueTarget>4</DialogueTarget>
			</DialogueOption>
		</DialogueOptionsList>
	</DialogueNode>

	<DialogueNode>
		<Name>4</Name>
		<Dialogue>
			<Page>If you are the Grand Traveller, you will know what it is</Page>
		</Dialogue>
		<DialogueOptionsList>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>...I don't.</Text>
				<DialogueTarget>5</DialogueTarget>
			</DialogueOption>
		</DialogueOptionsList>
	</DialogueNode>

	<DialogueNode>
		<Name>2</Name>
		<Dialogue>
			<Page>I am Cedar, the Keeper of the Light.</Page>
		</Dialogue>
		<DialogueOptionsList>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>What's the Light?</Text>
				<DialogueTarget>6</DialogueTarget>
			</DialogueOption>
		</DialogueOptionsList>
	</DialogueNode>

	<DialogueNode>
		<Name>6</Name>
		<Dialogue>
			<Page>The Light is our greatest treasure. It is the boundary between us and the heavens of our ancestors. The Light hosts The Pot of Chaos, making it worship it so. The Light has always been our lands' sibiling, as it has always been in the same spot in the sky for the entirety of our time. It gives life, we take it.</Page>
		</Dialogue>
		<DialogueOptionsList>
			<DialogueOption>
				<Text>It's actually a-...nevermind.</Text>
				<DialogueTarget>5</DialogueTarget>
			</DialogueOption>
		</DialogueOptionsList>
	</DialogueNode>
</DialogueTree>